A new cancer vaccine could train the immune system to see foreign cells
A new cancer vaccine could train the immune system to see foreign cells and kill them.
The vaccine trains the immune system to recognize foreign cells as part of the treatment.
The method involves removing immune cells from the patient and modifying them in a laboratory
Then they can see a protein that's common to many cancers and inject it back into the patient.
